<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="treat-vt">treat <strong><em>vt</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /triːt/    美 /triːt/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>对待；看待：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Treat other people as you hope they will treat you.
你希望别人如何对待你，你就如何对待别人。</p><footer>—— 伊索</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>All visitors to this village are <strong>treated with</strong> kindness.
到这个村子的所有游客都受到善待。</p><footer>2011 四川</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I really can’t understand you <strong>treating</strong> her <strong>like</strong> that. 
我真不明白你为何那样对她。</p><footer>2005 安徽</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Good public speaking training should <strong>treat</strong> you <strong>as</strong> a special one, with your own personal habits. 
好的公众演讲训练应该把你当作一个有着个人习惯的特殊个体来对待。</p><footer>2013 全国</footer></div>

<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>医治；治疗：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Which doctors are <strong>treating</strong> her <strong>for</strong> her illness? 
哪些医生在为她治病？</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The condition is usually <strong>treated with</strong> drugs and a strict diet. 
这种病情通常用药物和严格控制饮食进行治疗。</p></div>

<h4 id="3">3.★ <strong>(化学) 处理：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Beijing is able to treat 90 percent of waste water. 
北京有能力处理90%的废水。</p></div>

<h4 id="4">4.<strong>招待；款待；请 (客)：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Don’t worry about the cost; I’ll treat you. 
别担心费用，我请客。</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">固定搭配</h2>
<h3 id="treat-sb-to">treat sb to</h3>
<p>1.<strong>用…招待某人；以…款待某人：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>In a childlike act, she left the hospital and <strong>treated herself to</strong> a box of chocolates.
她孩子气地离开了医院，并给自己买了一盒巧克力糖吃。</p><footer>2010 湖南改</footer></div>

<h2 id="_3">真题解析</h2>
<ol>
<li>Young people should always  <strong><em>_</em></strong>_ (对待) the elders with respect.  （2015 陕西）  </li>
</ol>
<p>答案：
1. treat  </p></div>